{"lemma":"ضَبٌّ","slug":"ضَبٌّ","root":"ض.ب.ب","root_slug":"ض-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25428"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spiny-tailed lizard, mastigure (any lizard of the genus Uromastyx)","examples":[{"text":"876, The Letter of Yaʿqūb al-Layṯ to Al-Muʿtamid, written by the poet Ibrāhīm ibn Mamšāḏ\nفعودوا الى ارضكم بالحجاز\nلاكل الضباب ورعي الغنم\nSo return to your [own] land in Hejaz [Arabia], to eat lizards and to graze [your] sheep"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cleave to, to hold to firmly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have a gentle or scanty flow, to stream, to discharge sluggishly","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be affected by the disease termed ضَبّ (ḍabb)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a disease in the lips, in consequence of which blood flows from it","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tumor in the extremity of the foot of a camel","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chapping or cracking in the armpit of a child or camel","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spadix of a palm-tree before it cleaves open","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rancour, malice, anger, wrath (a characteristic ascribed to the mastigure)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَبَّ (ḍabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to milk with five fingers","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَبَّ (ḍabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṣ́abb-. Compare Classical Syriac ܥܒܐ (ʿabbā, “spiny-tailed lizard”) and Hebrew צַב (ṣaḇ, “turtle”)."},"ipa":["/dˤabb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25428","headword_ar":"ضَبٌّ","root":"Db","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of lizard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"termed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lacerta caudiverbera,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from its habit of striking with its tail; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jara$a","text_ar":"جَرَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) Forskål (Descr. Animalium,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1762},{"kind":"text","text":"p. 13,) terms it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lacerta Aegyptia;"},{"kind":"text","text":"referring to Hasselquist, p. 302; and adds the following description: “ femora teretia sine verrucis: cauda verticillata non longa: squamæ patentes, subconicæ mucronatæ: corpus nudum, rugosum: ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain reptile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small creeping thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$araAt","text_ar":"حَشَرَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waral","text_ar":"وَرَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not so long"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiro*awn","text_ar":"حِرْذَون"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which there are two species, one of the size of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr*wn","text_ar":"حرذون"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and one larger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) accord. to 'Abd-El-Káhir,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the size of a little young crocodile; having a tail like the tail of the latter: it assumes various colours when exposed to the sun, like as does the chameleon; lives seven hundred years; drinks not water, being satisfied with the air; voids one drop of urine in every forty days; its teeth consist of one curved piece; when it has quitted its hole it knows it not; and it lays eggs, like a bird:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so say IKh and Dmr and others: AM says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waral","text_ar":"وَرَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of a lank make, with a long tail; the latter resembling that of a serpent; and the length of some exceeds two cubits; but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tail of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is jointed, and its utmost length is a span:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Arabs deem the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wrl","text_ar":"ورل"},{"kind":"text","text":"a foul and filthy thing, and do not eat it; but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are eager to hunt and eat the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this animal has a rough tail, serrated with jags resembling vertebræ; its colour inclines to a blackish dusty hue; and when it becomes fat, its breast becomes yellow; it eats nothing but"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the locusts called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAdib","text_ar":"جَنَادِب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and young locusts before their wings have grown"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabFA","text_ar":"دَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and herbage, not venomous or noxious reptiles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wrl","text_ar":"ورل"},{"kind":"text","text":"eats scorpions and serpents and chameleons and beetles:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its flesh is an antidote against poisons, and women grow fat upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is the longest, of the animals, in retaining the remains of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTab~ixN","text_ar":"مُطَبِّخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb, K:) and the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDub~N","text_ar":"اَضُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAbN","text_ar":"ضِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dub~aAnN","text_ar":"ضُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last Lh particularizes as used to denote a great number, but ISd sees no reason for this distinction, (TA,) and [quasipl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDab~apN","text_ar":"مَضَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoxN","text_ar":"شَيْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) this last on the authority of As, as heard by him from more than one of the Arabs. (TA.) Hence one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN xab~N Dab~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ خَبٌّ ضَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A very deceitful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischievous, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an abominable, guileful, ireful man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a very deceitful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischievous"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked, and guileful man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) likened to the [lizard called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"on account of his guilefulness: and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN xab~apN Dab~apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ خَبَّةٌ ضَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodaEu mina AlD~ab~i","text_ar":"اَخْدَعُ مِنَ الضَّبِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More guileful than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, TA:) a prov. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaq~u mino","text_ar":"اَعَقُّ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~K","text_ar":"ضَبٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More undutiful to kindred than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"often eats its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husuwl","text_ar":"حُسُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or young ones when they have just come forth from the eggs]: another prov.: (S:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw HisolK","text_ar":"اَبُو حِسْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a surname of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowalu","text_ar":"اَطْوَلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*amaA='F mina AlD~ab~i","text_ar":"ذَمَا=ءً مِنَ الضَّبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", another prov. [expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*mY","text_ar":"ذمى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoyaru mino Dab~K","text_ar":"اَحْيَرُ مِنْ ضَبٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is likewise a prov. [expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hyr","text_ar":"حير"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 166.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atuEolimuniY biDab~K A^anaA Hara$otuhu","text_ar":"اَتُعْلِمُنِى بِضَبٍّ اَنَا حَرَشْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", another prov. [expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr$","text_ar":"حرش"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu Hat~aY yaHin~a","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ حَتَّى يَحِنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~ab~u fiY A_ivori AlA_ibili AlS~aAdirapi","text_ar":"الضَّبُّ فِى اـِثْرِ الاـِبِلِ الصَّادِرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it until the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utters a yearning cry at the heels of the camels returning from water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu Hat~aY","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ حَتَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarida AlD~ab~u","text_ar":"يَرِدَ الضَّبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it until the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comes to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. I will never do it:] because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not drink water. (S, O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~u AlD~ab~i","text_ar":"كَفُّ الضَّبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paw of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: to this the Arabs liken the hand of the niggard when he fails to give: (TA:) and it is also applied by way of comparison to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a niggard"},{"kind":"text","text":"himself: and to denote (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shortness and littleness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latent in the heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) like the [lizard called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"hiding itself in the furthest extremity of its hole: (A:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anger, wrath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rancour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement rancour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and enmity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dib~N","text_ar":"ضِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAbN","text_ar":"ضِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibabN","text_ar":"ضِبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, for] the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~N minohumaA HaAmilu DibabK liSaAHibihi","text_ar":"كُلٌّ مِنْهُمَا حَامِلُ ضِبَبٍ لِصَاحِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of them a bearer of latent rancours"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards his fellow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] occurs in a trad. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the lip,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which it flows with blood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swells, and becomes hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry and hard, and flows with blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tumour in the breast of a camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tumour"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuf~","text_ar":"خُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in copies of the K [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anf","text_ar":"انف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is, I doubt not, a mistranscription],) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firosin","text_ar":"فِرْسِن"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which means the same, or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the foot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease in the elbow of a camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be its cutting into his skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by rubbing against it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its being distorted, and falling against his side, so as to gall it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chapping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cracking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinafitaAqN","text_ar":"اِنَفِتَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the crease"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the armpit"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a child, or of a camel],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and abundance of flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) El- 'Adebbes El-Kinánee gives the same explanation, and says that this is what is also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAgiTN","text_ar":"ضَاغِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 5.])       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spadix,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the palm-tree: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAbN","text_ar":"ضِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~apN","text_ar":"ضَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (K, TA,) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~N","text_ar":"ضَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [but the latter seems to be a coll. gen. n., and the former its n. un.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe of a palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it cleaves open"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariyD","text_ar":"غَرِيض"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spadix"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Msb","L","O","K","Mgh","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}